Five men robbed the business in the Greenacres Shopping Centre on Thursday and held staff at gunpoint. CAPE TOWN - Jewellery worth more than R4 million has been stolen during an armed robbery at a Port Elizabeth jewellery store. Five men robbed the business in the Greenacres Shopping Centre on Thursday and held staff at gunpoint. No one was injured during the heist. The police's Priscilla Naidu said: “It is alleged that the suspects got into a white Renault Clio and sped off. We are investigating a case of armed robbery.” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)